The paper deals with the construction of MDS codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the sub-packetization level, which is related to the storage and retrieval of data, making categories such as cs.DS (data structures) and cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) likely. The paper also mentions field sizes, which are relevant to networked systems and communication protocols, making categories such as cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) and cs.SI (social and information networks) possible as well.
